                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v11w58b/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>for the simple reason that<lb/> I do not possess a photographic<lb/> portrait of\n                either myself or my<lb/> better half—besides, I am afraid<lb/> you would find my\n                exchange if<lb/> not looking exactly like <persName>Isaac's</persName><lb/> of old,\n                yet having something<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">sheepish</hi> about it. As soon as<lb/> I have copies I will\n                send them.<lb/> I have just had the inexpressible<lb/> pleasure of receiving home\n                a<lb/> capital likeness—more beautifully<lb/> &amp; successfully done—of my\n                late<lb/> father <add>ע\"ה</add>. It was taken from<lb/> a photograph done some 17\n                years<lb/> ago, and is a faithful representation<lb/> of what he was at that\n                period.<lb/> The copy just done for me is<lb/> also by a Jewish artist, a\n                member<lb/> of my congregation, and is life size.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v11w58b/canvas/p2"
                }
